atic oversight, rapidly diminishing budgets, and waves of technological distraction, The Craft of University Teaching provokes reflection on matters of pedagogy that are too often taken as settled. In so doing, it seeks to reclaim teaching as the intellectually vibrant and intrinsically rewarding endeavor that it is.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCollege teaching. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh  acheating.  acraft perspective.  aeducation.  ahigher education.  amethods.  apedagogy.  ateaching.  atechnology.  auniversity instruction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060679940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751749640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487517496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487517496.jpg  a978-3-11-060679-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles